cgen - A Cargo-style C project generator written in Bash

Features:
- cgen new <project>: create a new project directory with Makefile and source
- cgen build: builds the project
- cgen run: builds and runs the project
- cgen clean: removes the build artifacts
- cgen format: formats all .c and .h files using clang-format (if configured)

Installation:
- Copy the 'cgen' script to somewhere in your $PATH, e.g. ~/.local/bin
- Make it executable: chmod +x ~/.local/bin/cgen

Requirements:
- gcc
- make
- clang-format (optional, only for 'cgen format')

